2026-05-26 | Minimum Toggles to Partition Binary Array

	Question
Return minimum toggles needed.
	Key Insight
Choose a partition point:
		left side should become all 0s
		right side should become all 1s
For every partition:
- count 1s on left
		(these must become 0)
- count 0s on right
		(these must become 1)
Minimum among all partitions is answer.
	Approach
1.	Precompute:
		prefixOnes[i]
		= number of 1s till i
2.	Precompute:
		suffixZeros[i]
		= number of 0s from i onward
3.	Try every partition:
		toggles =
				ones on left
				+
				zeros on right
4.	Return minimum toggles.
	Time Complexity
	O(n)
	Space Complexity
	O(n)
	Solution
class Solution {
public:
    int minToggle(vector<int>& arr) {
        int n = arr.size();
        vector<int> prefixOnes(n + 1, 0);
        vector<int> suffixZeros(n + 1, 0);
        for(int i = 0; i < n; i++){
            prefixOnes[i + 1] =
                prefixOnes[i] + (arr[i] == 1);
        }
        for(int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--){
            suffixZeros[i] =
                suffixZeros[i + 1] + (arr[i] == 0);
        }
        int ans = INT_MAX;
        for(int i = 0; i <= n; i++){
            int toggles =
                prefixOnes[i] +
                suffixZeros[i];
            ans = min(ans, toggles);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
	Key Insight
At every partition point:
		left side must contain only 0s
		right side must contain only 1s  
So we simply count:
		wrong elements on each sid
